(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on comparing male and female reproductive roles.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in sexual reproduction, fertilization, and development that) Tj
T*
(the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Reproduction step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on reproductive structures and processes.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid mixing fertilization with implantation or growth stages while) Tj
T*
(solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Reproduction: sexual reproduction, fertilization,) Tj
T*
(and development.) Tj
T*
(- Mixing fertilization with implantation or growth stages.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Reproduction without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Reproduction in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around reproductive structures and processes before trying) Tj
T*
(harder tasks.) Tj
T*
